12/10/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov and his Greek counterpart, Costis Stephanopoulos, held talks in Sofia on Monday (11 October) and agreed on the need to enhance bilateral economic relations.
Parvanov told reporters afterwards that Stephanopoulos had pledged that construction of a new border checkpoint at Ilinden-Exochi -- delayed on the Greek side -- would be completed early next year.
In other news Monday, Bulgaria's Constitutional Court struck down legal texts which were reportedly seeking to introduce government control over the constitutionally independent judiciary.
Both the finance and justice ministries purportedly would have had oversight roles.
(Sega - 12/10/04;
Mediapool, MPA - 11/10/04)
